when compiling (& linking) with math.h, you need to type
'gcc __.c -lm'
'-l' tells the linker to use 'lib' prefix with '.a' or '.so' extension,
and 'm' is to specify which file it applies to. 
math.h is precompiled(?) as 'libm', and '-lm' means 'lib prefix followed by m'

source: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10409032/why-am-i-getting-undefined-reference-to-sqrt-error-even-though-i-include-math